title: Est Hotel 3*
description:
The "Est Hotel" is a standard 3 stars hotel and particularly practical for groups and individual persons with a low budget.
The location is pretty practical due to the proximity of the East and North train stations (Eurostar), next to Grands Boulevards, the Halles, and the Centre Pompidou.

http://esthotelparis.parishotelinn.com/

Metro:
Jacques Bonsergent‎ (M5);
Château d'Eau‎ (M4);
Gare de l'Est‎ (M4, M5, M7).

urlhtml: The Tonic Hotel in Les Halles and near the Lourve
title: The Tonic Hotel in Les Halles and near the Lourve
description: We stayed here years ago and it is a quaint boutique hotel near Les Halles, within walking distane of the Pompidou Center and the Lourve. It is so small that we had to go up in the elevator and out luggage followed. It served a small breakfast as well. Loved it!! No AC but we went to the local department store that is closed, to buy a fan.

title: Le Bouquet des Archives
description: Typical neighbourhood bar/bistro. Regular lunch clientele, mainly local businesspeople, a few tourists. Gets more raffish in the evening.
